TXB-HLC-TP_29,"4.1.2.15","Health Monitoring  -   Voice Alerts and Warnings Display  ",,,,,,,,,

TXB-HLC-TP_8217,"4.1.2.15.0-1",,"Test Strategy","Information",,"1) Health monitor- Voice Alerts & Display test cases are verified using the following procedures at high level: HM_HL_TEST_NOM_Procedure HM_HL_TEST_MIN_Procedure HM_HL_TEST_MAX_Procedure These tests are performed as component tests using RTRT. The calibration data is varied by changing the values of Calibration Variables to its Nominal, Minimal and Maximum values within the PTU file.",,,,,

TXB-HLC-TP_8218,"4.1.2.15.0-3.0-1",,"Test Plan","Information",,"The test is to be done on the file ‘hm_context.c’ present in ‘Simulink\Code\App\appHealthMonitor’. The function hm_context_initialize is invoked to check the default output variable initialisations and then hm_context_step will have to be invoked to check the functionality by setting the calibration variables to their Nominal values as per the table above. There are no other interfaces available to invoke. ",,,,,
TXB-HLC-TP_4430,"4.1.2.15.0-3.1",,,"Test Procedure",,"Follow the process which mentioned in the Appendix 5.6 for the RTRT test procedure
Set smd_enum_safetyFailReason to SM_EXCEED_LOAD_LIMIT_E","At the end of cycle 1

system is in PCM(MM_SYSTEM_MODE_TURRET_STEER_E) mode AND  vehicle headset1 is INVALID AND headset2 is INVALID, set following alarts on fifth priority.
